    <node id="Newtons Method">
      <data key="d0">Newtons Method</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Newton's Method is a faster alternative algorithm for fitting models like logistic regression, utilizing derivatives to find optimal values.&lt;SEP&gt;Newton’s Method is an iterative numerical method used for finding successively better approximations to the roots (or zeroes) of a real-valued function.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-023cc775f8b1adeebc9c45d2e9f6fe90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d9737bbcc99dd55bb4b79cf055977a2</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1767942407</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Gradient Ascent">
      <data key="d0">Gradient Ascent</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Gradient Ascent is an optimization algorithm used for finding the maximum of a function by iteratively moving in the direction of the steepest ascent.&lt;SEP&gt;Gradient Ascent is an algorithm used for optimizing models, mentioned as a viable option but contrasted with another method.&lt;SEP&gt;Gradient Ascent is an optimization algorithm used to find the maximum of a function, often applied in machine learning models.&lt;SEP&gt;Gradient Ascent is an optimization algorithm used to find the maximum of a function by iteratively moving in the direction of the steepest ascent.&lt;SEP&gt;Gradient ascent is a mathematical optimization technique used to maximize the likelihood in model training.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-023cc775f8b1adeebc9c45d2e9f6fe90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac0a1ea80eae7c222bf0ffd73875b023&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d9737bbcc99dd55bb4b79cf055977a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1aa4c1f1bcccecc7faef4f12ad096763&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d65cfad802d1335db113217e2cb6afbe</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1767942407</data>
