    <node id="Exponential Family Distribution">
      <data key="d0">Exponential Family Distribution</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The exponential family distribution is a group of probability distributions that can be expressed in a specific mathematical form, allowing for flexibility in modeling.&lt;SEP&gt;The Exponential Family Distribution is a class of distributions that includes the Gaussian, mentioned in relation to various statistical properties.&lt;SEP&gt;The Exponential Family Distribution is a class of probability distributions that can be characterized by certain parameters, used in various statistical models.&lt;SEP&gt;Exponential family distribution is a class of probability distributions characterized by a specific functional form, often used in statistical modeling.&lt;SEP&gt;Exponential Family Distribution refers to a class of probability distributions that includes many commonly used distributions in statistics and is useful for modeling outcomes with dependencies.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-023cc775f8b1adeebc9c45d2e9f6fe90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49f40563b7c8469bddeeb04d56b3cec7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1dcfa4fdc2012c4e3a3c336e39e4afec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-486f08627d119b0879789e4cf88e8904&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38d7cccd02d2282bbd339ef51ba43f85</data>
