    <node id="Theta">
      <data key="d0">Theta</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Theta is a variable representing parameters that are being estimated or optimized within the context of the algorithms.&lt;SEP&gt;Theta is a parameter discussed in the context of probability and is determined as a function of phi.&lt;SEP&gt;Theta is a parameter in statistical modeling that represents the relationships defined in regression models.&lt;SEP&gt;Theta is a set of parameters that plays a critical role in statistical models, such as logistic regression.&lt;SEP&gt;Theta represents the parameters in the statistical models, influencing the probabilities computed in softmax regression.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ac0a1ea80eae7c222bf0ffd73875b023&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d9737bbcc99dd55bb4b79cf055977a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-674af09a64beddbff4e4e4b6e543709a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e92ae48716b56f03feed3a2648edf8bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb276908b4dcc65a416b2c0490f93e3a</data>
