      <data key="d2">Y is the output variable in classification problems, often taking on binary values of zero or one.&lt;SEP&gt;Y is a variable whose properties are discussed in relation to sufficient statistics and probability distributions.&lt;SEP&gt;Y is a variable representing one of the K possible values used in the context of statistical functions.&lt;SEP&gt;Y is a random variable used in the context of softmax regression, taking on one of K possible values.</data>
