    </node>
    <node id="Exponential Distribution">
      <data key="d0">Exponential Distribution</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The Exponential Distribution is a continuous probability distribution that is commonly used to model the time between independent events in a Poisson process.&lt;SEP&gt;The Exponential Distribution is a continuous probability distribution often used to model time until an event occurs.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-486f08627d119b0879789e4cf88e8904&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb276908b4dcc65a416b2c0490f93e3a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1767942411</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Generalized Linear Model">
      <data key="d0">Generalized Linear Model</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The Generalized Linear Model (GLM) is a flexible generalization of ordinary linear regression that allows for response variables to have error distribution models other than normal.&lt;SEP&gt;The Generalized Linear Model is a flexible generalization of ordinary linear regression for modeling various distributions.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-486f08627d119b0879789e4cf88e8904&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb276908b4dcc65a416b2c0490f93e3a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1767942411</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Input X">
      <data key="d0">Input X</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Input X represents the predictor variables or features in a statistical model, influencing the predicted outcome.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-486f08627d119b0879789e4cf88e8904</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1767942411</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Response Variable Y">
      <data key="d0">Response Variable Y</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The Response Variable Y is the output or dependent variable that is being predicted or modeled in relation to the input variables.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-486f08627d119b0879789e4cf88e8904</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1767942411</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Wisha Distribution">
      <data key="d0">Wisha Distribution</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The Wisha Distribution is a probability distribution that models distributions over covariance matrices, belonging to the exponential family.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-486f08627d119b0879789e4cf88e8904</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1767942411</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Softmax Regression">
      <data key="d0">Softmax Regression</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Softmax Regression is a statistical method used for multi-class classification problems, generalizing logistic regression to handle K classes instead of just two.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-674af09a64beddbff4e4e4b6e543709a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1767942411</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Parameterization by Theta">
      <data key="d0">Parameterization by Theta</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Parameterization by Theta refers to the process of defining a statistical model using parameters represented by theta, which influence the probabilities in softmax regression.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-674af09a64beddbff4e4e4b6e543709a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1767942411</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Indicator Functions">
      <data key="d0">Indicator Functions</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Indicator Functions are binary functions that take the value of one for specific conditions and zero otherwise, used in calculating probabilities in softmax regression.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-674af09a64beddbff4e4e4b6e543709a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1767942412</data>
