    <node id="Sufficient Statistic">
      <data key="d0">Sufficient Statistic</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A sufficient statistic is a function of the data that captures all necessary information for parameter estimation in a statistical model.&lt;SEP&gt;A sufficient statistic summarizes information from a sample to make inferences about a population parameter.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-38d7cccd02d2282bbd339ef51ba43f85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e92ae48716b56f03feed3a2648edf8bd</data>
