      <data key="d9">discrete variable,statistical concept</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-1dcfa4fdc2012c4e3a3c336e39e4afec</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1767942419</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Parson Distribution" target="Generalized Linear Model">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The Parson Distribution serves as a model within the framework of the Generalized Linear Model, particularly for count data.</data>
      <data key="d9">modeling,statistical application</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-486f08627d119b0879789e4cf88e8904</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1767942420</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Gamma Distribution" target="Exponential Distribution">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Both the Gamma and Exponential Distributions are part of the family of distributions utilized to model positive numbers in various statistical contexts.</data>
      <data key="d9">modeling,probability distributions</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-486f08627d119b0879789e4cf88e8904</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1767942420</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Gamma Distribution" target="Logistic Regression Algorithm">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The Logistic Regression Algorithm can also utilize a Gamma Distribution for modeling depending on the characteristics of the data.</data>
      <data key="d9">alternative,statistical modeling</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-cb276908b4dcc65a416b2c0490f93e3a</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1767942430</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Exponential Distribution" target="Logistic Regression Algorithm">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The Logistic Regression Algorithm may be adapted to use the Exponential Distribution based on the nature of the response variable.</data>
      <data key="d9">alternative,statistical modeling</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-cb276908b4dcc65a416b2c0490f93e3a</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1767942431</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Generalized Linear Model" target="Canonical Link Function">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The Generalized Linear Model uses the Canonical Link Function to relate linear predictors with the response variable.</data>
